    "Management": {
      "text": "Artificial tears 5-6x per day\nNaphazoline/pheniramine 0.025%/0.3% drops 4x daily\nCold compresses\nConsider topical antibiotic if unable to differentiate from bacterial conjunctivitis\nFrequent hand-washing (highly contagious)",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Follow-up with ophtho if worsening or no improvement in 7 days\nViral conjunctivitis is highly contagious. Patients may return to work or school after discharge from eye(s) has resolved. Advise good hygiene practices and avoid close contact with very old, very young, or other immunocompromised individuals.",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
